President Muhammadu Buhari is currently meeting with state governors from the 36 states of the federation. The meeting, which is holding at the council chambers of the Presidential Villa, Abuja, started at about 12:40 p.m. The meeting is expected to discuss a new minimum wage for Nigerian workers. Week back, a presidential committee set up by the government under the leadership of a former Head of Service of the Federation, Ama Pepple, had recommended that the new minimum wage should be increased from N18,000 to N30,000 